# Atlassian API Access

When accessing Confluence or Jira content, ALWAYS use the API credentials from `.env`:

- `JIRA_EMAIL` - Email for authentication
- `JIRA_API_TOKEN` - API token for authentication  
- `JIRA_BASE_URL` - Base URL (https://global-e.atlassian.net)

## Confluence API Examples

Fetch a page by ID:
```bash
curl -s -u "$JIRA_EMAIL:$JIRA_API_TOKEN" \
  "$JIRA_BASE_URL/wiki/api/v2/pages/{pageId}?body-format=storage"
```

Search Confluence:
```bash
curl -s -u "$JIRA_EMAIL:$JIRA_API_TOKEN" \
  "$JIRA_BASE_URL/wiki/rest/api/content/search?cql=text~'search term'"
```

## DO NOT

- Do not use browser navigation to access Confluence/Jira (requires login)
- Do not ask user to authenticate MCP tools for Atlassian
- Do not ask user for credentials - they are in .env
